Eagle Materials, Inc. (EXP) Reaches $91.75 After 6.00% Down Move, Tiger Management Lifted By $2.94 Million Its Shire Plc (SHPG) Position


					
						July 26, 2017 - By Vivian Park

The stock of Eagle Materials, Inc. (NYSE:EXP) is a huge mover today! About 176,905 shares traded. Eagle Materials, Inc. (NYSE:EXP) has risen 36.20% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 19.50% the S&P500.The move comes after 7 months negative chart setup for the $4.55B company. It was reported on Jul, 26 by Barchart.com. We have $86.25 PT which if reached, will make NYSE:EXP worth $273.00M less.







Tiger Management Llc increased Shire Plc (SHPG) stake by 22.14% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Tiger Management Llc acquired 17,300 shares as Shire Plc (SHPG)’s stock rose 4.45%. The Tiger Management Llc holds 95,454 shares with $16.26 million value, up from 78,154 last quarter. Shire Plc now has $51.78B valuation. The stock rose 1.72% or $2.86 reaching $168.97 per share. About 821,846 shares traded. Shire PLC (ADR) (NASDAQ:SHPG) has risen 4.69% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 12.01% the S&P500.
